@node "Intro" "Introduction"

 @{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

  I started using DOpus Magellan in 1997 and it was a hard job
  to find out all possibilities that this great, but very complex
  program hid in its code. So I started reading the very large
  manual very carefully and found some interesting features,
  you won't discover at once. One day I read the chapter about
  the DOpus ENV variables and found more and more features :)
  I missed the swazinfo patch, I used on my workbench and what
  I read about the 'UseWBInfo' variable, gave me some hope to
  use it again in DOpus.

  The only problem there existed now, was the following:
   I am not a friend of the shell, instead of using it
   sometimes. Everytime I wanted to change a variable,
   I had to open the shell and set these variables
   using the keyboard.

  The idea I had, when using the MUI-CGXPrefs program, that
  does the same job for other variables and software, but
  the principle was the same...
  So I started coding a little tool, that did the same thing,
  but slidely modified (see @{"FAQ" link "FAQ" 0}) for DOpus.

  I think many other people don't know all the possibilities
  that are hidden in this great workbench replacement, instead
  of Jonathan Potter itself :)
  So I decided to release this program to the public, that it
  would make usage of DOpus easier for the user.

  @{b}____________@{ub}

 @{b}@{u}DOpus piracy notice@{uu}@{ub}

  If you don't use this program or use this program in any illegal
  way, stop doing this, pay the price for a great utility and
  support the development and the developer of this program, that
  enhances your system like never seen before !

      Jens Weyer
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"

 @{b}@{u}System requirements@{ub}@{uu}

  If you want to use this program, you should have the following
  min. configuration:

     OS:     3.0+
            (3.1 advised)
     DOpus: Magellan Version (5.5+)
            (5.65 / 5.661 advised)

            This program includes some variables, that are
            only supported since version 5.5 of DOpus !
            Instead of that fact, you can use it, because
            DOpus will ignore unknown variables !
     RAM:   Here is only one sentence to say:
              more ram -> more possibilities :)

  I advise you to upgrade your DOpus version to 5.661 !
  You can download it via Internet at following pages:

     http://www.schatztruhe.de/updates.html
       (query to:)

     http://www.gpsoft.com.au/magellan/download.html

  Keep your registration number ready to enter !
@endnode

