@node "Usage" "Usage"

 @{b}@{u}Usage@{ub}@{uu}

  @{b}@{i}The menu@{ub}@{ui}

   @{b}@{u}Project@{ub}@{uu}

    @{b}About (ShortCut: AMIGA + ?)@{ub}

      Gives some version and copyright information about
      the program.

    @{b}Quit (ShortCut: AMIGA + Q)@{ub}

      Quits the program. If you've changed anything and you quit
      the program, the changed data won't be saved and you won't
      be asked or warned by the program !

   @{b}@{u}Data@{ub}@{uu}

    @{b}@{i}ENVars@{ub}@{ui}

     @{b}Save (ShortCut: AMIGA + S)@{ub}

       Saves the actual data on disk - writes in ENV: and
       ENVARC: and enables it to the system at once.
       (see @{"FAQ" link "FAQ" 0})

     @{b}Use (ShortCut: AMIGA + U)@{ub}

       Writes the actual data into ENV: and enables it to
       system at once. (WARNING ! Will be lost after a reboot !)
       (see @{"FAQ" link "FAQ" 0})

    @{b}@{i}Open with@{ub}@{ui}

     @{b}Save@{ub}

       Saves the actual 'Open with' list to disk (DOpus5:System/OpenWith).

       @{i}If you've made changes to the list, those won't
       appear until your next dopus session !@{ui}

  @{b}@{i}The gadgets@{ub}@{ui}

    @{b}Save (Hotkey: 'S' or 's')@{ub}

      See above.

    @{b}Use (Hotkey: 'E' or 'e')@{ub}

      See above.

    @{b}Checkmark gadgets@{ub}

      See @{"variables" link "ENVVars" 0}.

    @{b}Edit 'Open with'...@{ub}

      When pressing this button, a new window will be opened,
      where you can edit your popup's 'Open with' entries (if
      those exists).

      @{b}@{i}The 'Open with' window@{ui}@{ub}

        @{b}Open With entries@{ub}

          In this listview you can see your popup's Open With
          entries.

        @{b}Add@{ub}

          Let's you add a new entry to the list.

        @{b}Del@{ub}

          If an entry is selected and you press this gadget,
          that entry will be removed from the list.

        @{b}Up@{ub}

          If an entry is selected, you can move that entry
          towards the top of the list.

        @{b}Down@{ub}

          Does the same as 'Up', but towards the bottom of
          the list.

        @{b}Save@{ub}

          See above.

  @{b}____________________@{ub}

  @{b}@{i}The ToolType(s)@{ub}@{ui}

    @{b}HELP@{ub}

      With this tooltype you can specify the path of this
      amigaguide (if exists). If you have specified this
      and you press 'HELP' while using Do5extPrefs, the
      program will start multiview with this guide as
      database.

@endnode

@node "ENVVars" "Variables"

 @{b}@{u}Variables@{ub}@{uu}

  @{b}@{i}NoNoLabel@{ub}@{ui}

    Deactivates icons without description.
    You are now able to correct a little bug - reported by users -
    that icons without description were shown. Perhaps the bit set
    by DOpus was altered by another program.

  @{b}@{i}PopUpDelay@{ub}@{ui}

    Delays the popup of a popupmenu with the value set by the user
    in 1/50 secs. (Default: 10 = 1/5 sec.).

  @{b}@{i}WorkbenchTitle@{ub}@{ui}

    If this variable is set, DOpus won't generate its own screentitle
    and mem-usage / clock in the title bar. Instead of that, the screen-
    title will be set to 'Amiga Workbench'. So patches - like the MCP
    'ChangeWBTitle' function can be used in DOpus as workbench replacement.
    (BUT comments like 'Loading program '.....'' won't be displayed then)

  @{b}@{i}QuickIconDrag@{ub}@{ui}

    If this variable is set, icons won't be masked by dragging. So the
    icon has a transparent background (like workbench) and is faster.

  @{b}@{i}NoCustomDrag@{ub}@{ui}

    If this variable is set, the RTG-icondragfunctions will be deactivated
    at all.

  @{b}@{i}UseWBInfo@{ub}@{ui}

    If this variable is set, DOpus will call the WBInfo()-function instead
    of its own icon.module. Works only, if workbench is running and you use
    V39 of the Amiga-OS. You can use patches like SwazInfo with this.

  @{b}@{i}ShowUseDatatypesFirst@{ub}@{ui}

    If this variable is set, DOpus will try to load any picture using your
    system datatypes. If not set, DOpus will use its show.module.

  @{b}@{i}3DLook@{ub}@{ui}

    Special flag to provide compatibility with programs like SysIHack.

  @{b}@{i}NoMUFS@{ub}@{ui}

    Flag to disable the multiuser filesystem.

  @{b}@{i}Benefy@{ub}@{ui}

    Flag to shorten the (message) menu titles to fit into the titlebar
    of the window.

  @{b}@{i}HidepadLock@{ub}@{ui}

    Flag to not have the padlock added to lister titlebars.

  @{b}@{i}CommandLineLength@{ub}@{ui}

    Defines the maximum length of command lines in AmigaDOS functions
    (Default: 512).

  @{b}@{i}IconSpaceX@{ub}@{ui}

    Let's you define the horizontal spacing between icons
    (Default: 3)

  @{b}@{i}IconSpaceY@{ub}@{ui}

    Let's you define the vertical spacing between icons
    (Default: 5)

  @{b}@{i}IconGridX@{ub}@{ui}

    Flag to make DOpus align icons to a horizontal grid when
    positioning them automatically.

  @{b}@{i}IconGridY@{ub}@{ui}

    Flag to make DOpus align icons to a vertical grid when
    positioning them automatically.

  @{b}@{i}PatchWBInfo@{ub}@{ui}

    Flag, that allows to use DOpus Info by other programs.

  @{b}@{i}DOSPatch@{ub}@{ui}

    Flag to turn on the dynamic refresh for listers
    (i.e. the lister is continually refreshed as actions are
     performed instead of when they are completed)

  @{b}______________@{ub}

  @{b}@{u}Existing, but not supported variables:@{ub}@{uu}

  @{b}@{i}ListerEditing@{ub}@{ui}

    Flag to enable direct editing of filenames in a lister.

    @{i}(Removed, because you can set this using DOpus'
    built-in preferences (Settings/Environment/ListerOptions))

    Reported by Dariusz Gac

  @{b}______________@{ub}

  @{b}@{i}I don't know, if the above hits any copyright notice. If it
  does, please @{fg shine}@{"report" link "Author" 0}@{fg text} at once and I will remove it !!!@{ub}@{ui}
@endnode

@node "FAQ" "FAQ"

 @{b}@{u}@{fg shine}F@{fg text}requently @{fg shine}A@{fg text}sked @{fg shine}Q@{fg text}uestions@{ub}@{uu}

  Q: I have some trouble with the GUI !
  R: This program needs OS 3.0+ and GadTools Library
     V39+ to run - @{b}but@{ub} it is possible, that it uses
     some V40 TAGS. I don't think, that it will influence
     the function of this tool.

  Q: I set the 'UseWBInfo' Flag to 0, but nothing happens,
     if I call 'Information' in DOpus' popupmenu !
  R: That's a problem caused by DOpus ! I don't know why,
     but if the ENV var was set by my program, it seems
     like DOpus always trys to call the WbInfo()-function.
     So, if you have that problem, just delete the following
     file in ENV and ENVARC after boot: 'DOpus/UseWBInfo'
     and everything works.

     Just click @{"here" system "Delete ENV:DOpus/UseWBInfo ENVARC:DOpus/UseWBInfo"} to execute this.

  Q: I found more variables than used in your program !
  R: That's right. There are 2 or 3 variables, that aren't
     supported by this program, because they contain private
     data of DOpus, that should not be altered.

     It can also happen, that there are some variables, that
     I don't know, because I couldn't find them in the DOpus
     manual (like NoMUFS, Benefy).
@endnode

@node "DOexpans" "DOpus expansions"

 @{b}@{u}DOpus expansions@{ub}@{uu}

  This program is an expansion for DOpus, for example. I know,
  that this chapter does not really belong to this guide, but
  I found a lot of such expansions in Aminet. Some are very
  useful others are really sh** ...

  So I decided to include a chapter with tested and improved
  expansions for DOpus:

   @{b}@{i}ARexx / DOS@{ub}@{ui}

    ArcDir.lha

      IMHO one of the best expansions for DOpus. It presents
      the contents of an Lha or Lzx archive in an DOpus Lister
      and you can use it like a normal part of your system -
      unpacked ! You can also add, delete, read and extract
      data from there to anywhere you want. Use it and you
      won't miss it !

    CD_MM_OPUS5.lha

      This archive contains programs and arexx scripts for
      multimedia play of audio and video (mpeg) data !
      You can also use ti to convert some audio formats !

    xpkdopus.lha

      If you have installed this archive, you can handle
      the complete xpk power with some clicks !
      You can (de)crunch and (de)crypt files. But the best
      thing is: you click a file, crunched with xpk and DOpus
      will (thanks to xpkdopus script) decrunch it automatically.
      If you have crunched and crypted a file, DOpus asks for
      the password to decrunch and will display it then.
      It's great !!!

    MPEGA-GUIplay.lha

      With the content of this archive you can play MPEG-sound
      files within a click and you will get all important data
      with progressbar and information.

      You also need the program 'MPEGA' for playing and an extra
      archive from Aminet at 'util/cli/TBreak.lha' !

   @{b}@{i}Modules@{ub}@{ui}

    RndPic Module

      You are lazy about your dopus backgrounds, you see
      all the time and you can just change it by clicking
      through the preferences windows ?

      Use this module in your dopus5 system and those times
      will be gone ! It changes your backgrounds randomly !

      biz/dopus

    DeliPlay1.1.lha

      After the installation of this archive, you can use the
      complete DeliTracker power with DOpus. It adds new commands
      to DOpus and you can stear DeliTracker with some clicks
      or hotkeys !

    DEPlay.lzx

      This archive contains the successor of DeliPlay1.1.lha.
      It is an enhanced and reworked version, that doesn't
      contain an enforcer hit any more. Update, if you use it,
      at: @{i}http://home.t-online.de/home/hhummel/@{ui}

    Compare.lha

      This module allows you to compare two files and - if
      differences were found - displays the number of diffs.
      and outs them into DOpus reader.

      Useful.

    Hotlist.lha

      This module allows you to create a hotlist of your
      favourite directories, that are located 145 directories
      under root :) You just click one in the hotlist
      displayed dir and it will appear at once in a Lister !

   @{b}@{i}Graphics@{ub}@{ui}

    NewIconDoProgs.lha / NewIconDoTBar.lha

      These archives contain some very nice graphics made
      for usage with DOpus and NewIcons.

      Great !

      Now you can find the successors and childs of the
      packages I told you above on Aminet at biz/dopus !

      Check it out :)

  @{b}___________________@{ub}

@{b}@{i}@{fg shine}   Send @{"me" link "Author" 0} your suggestions and/or reports or testings of
   other expansions and I will include them here !!!@{ub}@{ui}@{fg text}
@endnode

