@node "Products" "Products"

 @{b}@{u}Products@{ub}@{uu}

  In this chapter, I want to present other programs
  I wrote.

  @{b}@{i}ARC@{ub}@{ui} (Aminet:util/misc)

   You write your readme files for your Aminet uploads
   yourself, and you don't really know, what is allowed
   or not ? You don't know all the flags and don't format
   the text style of your readme file. You can't add some
   archive information easily - like seen onto Aminet CDs ?

   Then use ARC - the ultimative AminetReadmeCreator !
   With possibility to load existing readme files !!!

  @{b}@{i}HFRemove@{ub}@{ui} (Aminet:util/wb)

   You know / use the fms system on your drive ?

   Then you know, that mounted fms units will exist on your
   workbench until the reboot. If you have a little workbench
   screen and want to get rid of the icons and units, that
   use memory and screen's space ?

   Then use HFRemove - it removes these units systemfriendly !

   It also has features like sleep mode (-> unpacking), running
   of HFMount and others !

  @{b}@{i}ActXDx@{ub}@{ui} (Aminet:util/wb)

   You use the xpk-disk system on your drive ?

   Then you know, that the icon(s) of mounted disk(s) won't
   appear at once. So use this tiny program. It needs all
   parameters as tooltypes for usage in the WBStartup.
   It activates one (at the moment) mounted disk and makes
   it ready for use (icon) on your workbench.

  @{b}@{i}AutoDiz@{ub}@{ui} (Aminet:util/arc)

   Tool, that handles File_ID.Diz' automatically.
   Easy to use and to install. Usage in DOpus, or other
   dirutils (btw - DOpus is MORE than a simple dirutil :)),
   shell or dos-/arexxscripts is very simple !
@endnode

