@node "Developers" "Developer information"

 @{b}@{u}Developer information@{ub}@{uu}

  Here you can read, which programs were used for the development
  of this program:

    GadToolsBox 2.1b
    MaxonC++ 4.0 Pro

  The new principle of ENVar saving:

                 Startup (initialisation of envars mem)
                     |
                Program runs...   <------|
                     |                   |
                 Save/Use clicked        |
                     |                   |
            PrepSetEnv(char *,int,int);  |
                     |                   |
            given Var already exists ?   |
                  /         \\            |
                Yes         No           |
                 |           |           |
              Default ?  Default ?       |
               /   \\       /    \\        |
             Yes   No     Yes   No       |
              |     |      |     |       |
          delete  change   |    create   |
          File    File     |    File     |
            \\       |    delete  /       |
             \\      |     File  /        |
              \\     |      |   /         |
               \\    |      |  /          |
                \\___|______|_/           |
                       |                 |
                     return;--------------


  @{fg shine}Source code is included@{fg text}.
@endnode

@node "History" "History"

  @{b}@{u}History@{ub}@{uu}

   You can read the steps of development until now here:

   @{i}@{b}version 1.6@{ub}@{ui}
     Added new ENVar (@{"PatchWBInfo" link "ENVVars" 87})
     Removed ENVar (@{"ListerEditing" link "ENVVars" 101})
     (Dariusz Gac)
     Transformed IconGridX/Y into integer
     (Trevor Morris)
     Re-arranged GUI

     Fixed Heddley errors in guide

   @{i}@{b}Version 1.5@{ub}@{ui}
     Added the @{"'Open With' edit functions" link "Usage" 57}
     Re-arranged menu

   @{i}@{b}Version 1.4@{ub}@{ui}
     Added new ENVar (@{"DOSPatch" link "ENVVars" 91})
     Re-arranged gadgets (suggested by Trevor Morris)
     Reworked Save-function - works now properly
     (Thanks to Trevor Morris)

   @{i}@{b}Version 1.3@{ub}@{ui}
     Added new ENVar (@{"ListerEditing" link "ENVVars" 101})
     Added 'HELP'-Key Support (@{"ToolType HELP" link "Usage" 95})

   @{i}@{b}Version 1.2@{ub}@{ui}
     Added 6 Vars, that I didn't know
     (@{"CommandLineLength" link "ENVVars" 62}, @{"HidepadLock" link "ENVVars" 58}, @{"IconSpaceX" link "ENVVars" 67}/@{"-Y" link "ENVVars" 72},
      @{"IconGridX" link "ENVVars" 77}/@{"-Y" link "ENVVars" 82})
     reported by Trevor Morris.
     Reworked the ENVar save routine.
     I did this, because many people weren't happy with
     the old handling (ALL vars were saved).
     This has CHANGED !
     It's a simple game:
      The program checks on startup the existing ENVars
      and remembers, if they already existed or not.
      If you've changed the var while using DO5extPrefs
      to it's default, the ENVar file will be simply
      deleted from the disk (safes disk space and reduces
      the number of files) or saved, if you changed the
      flag <> default.

   @{i}@{b}Version 1.1@{ub}@{ui}
